# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CarryGuard marketing site — Stripe payment link reference
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The marketing site at getcarryguard.com is a static HTML deployment on
# Vercel — there is no build step that injects environment variables, so
# these keys are NOT read at runtime by index.html.
#
# They are documented here for two reasons:
#   1. The in-app Expo client uses the same key names (prefixed with
#      EXPO_PUBLIC_) for its shared Stripe URL config.
#   2. If/when the site is migrated to Next.js, drop the NEXT_PUBLIC_
#      prefix in front and these will work directly.
#
# To update the actual URLs used by the static /subscribe page,
# edit /subscribe/config.js.

STRIPE_CARRIER_MONTHLY=https://buy.stripe.com/REPLACE_ME_CARRIER_MONTHLY
STRIPE_CARRIER_YEARLY=https://buy.stripe.com/REPLACE_ME_CARRIER_YEARLY
STRIPE_GUARDIAN_MONTHLY=https://buy.stripe.com/REPLACE_ME_GUARDIAN_MONTHLY
STRIPE_GUARDIAN_YEARLY=https://buy.stripe.com/REPLACE_ME_GUARDIAN_YEARLY
